- All static assets go in static/
- JavaScript goes in static/src/js/ organized by purpose  
- JS and SCSS are built with Vite only
- Use {% static 'path/to/asset' %} in Django templates
- Never add duplicate htmx:configRequest listeners — use HTMXManager only
- Page modules in static/src/js/pages/ must export initialize()
- Add new pages to pageInitializers in main.js
- Import HTMXManager only in main.js — components use window.htmxManager
- Use {% trans 'text' %} — do not use |trans (not a valid Django filter)
- Components with event listeners must handle htmx:reinitialize-[page] events
- Use selectors like [id^="prefix"] — never hardcode IDs in dynamic templates
- Manually set HTMX headers in JS when needed — they override defaults
- Do not manually build or insert HTMX request URLs in JavaScript
- Use native attributes like href, src, or action — HTMX reads these directly
- Let Django generate dynamic URLs server-side (e.g., {% url 'viewname' arg %})
